subject: p19016834
History: Evaluation of the patient with esophageal stent migration.
Findings: AP radiograph of the chest was compared to prior study obtained on at 00:47. The assessment of the position of the esophageal stent demonstrates minimal change as compared to the prior radiograph. Right chest tube is in place. The right internal jugular line is in place. There is interval improvement in the left base aeration that is most likely consistent with resolution of aspiration/atelectasis. No pneumothorax is appreciated. The ET tube tip is in place.
